<font color="#FF0000">ANSWER TO ART</font><br>
<tt>Tue Mar 11 23:10:25 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Arthur, I am both. And none. Thanks to interactions with the members of this site.  I stand by my first statement about being the voice in your ear, but I can no longer agree with the part about &quot;you suck&quot;. I have learned to not hate nor resent the vet.  I didn't use to, now I do. Thank you PBS and a few of you &quot;posters&quot; who taught this &quot;protestor&quot; some new ways to think about veterans.<br><br>
What I have posted recently, more reconcilitory, more non flaming, more rational and less emotional, is a lesson that I learned here. I learned that even the grunt in the jungle had something to tell me, even up on my &quot;moral high ground&quot;.<br>
I learned, also, that we are more related that I ever dared think we were.  I was the body laying in front of the train in Oakland, you were the bodies inside the train, at the induction center. I failed, and you did you.  We were both victimized.  I feel no regret for those days and deeds, and now, now, (as opposed to before), I understand you and can accept that you too feel no regret. <br><br>
I have also learned that I can admit growth, and being wrong, but some of you can't, and that saddens me.  DocDel says he is pulling off the site, that is too bad but perhaps not.  I did, for over a month, and when I came back, I saw the incredible angry crap I had written, some good, some not good, and I was confronted with me.  Like the old zen line, one is the sound of one hand slapping? It's the sound of your own hand striking your opening and stunned mouth.  This site and all of you let me to challenge my stale thoughts, just as I challenged Nurse Ratchet to grow up and talk truth.<br><br>
So Art, they are both me, and they are not.  One is pre doc, the other is current doc, God knows what future doc might say or do.   I'll try and catch up on #6 next day or two, it's been kind of busy down here in crazy land, and a shrink gots to do what a shrink does, whatever in the hell that is....but thanks Arthur, for your reply, and your thinking. <br><br>
doc
